

    
       
       By: Robert Louis Stevenson  Set in the background of the Scottish suffering at the hands of the English, this book tells the story of a young Whig David Balfour and how he befriends a dangerous jacobite who has got a bounty on his head, after his parents death and his uncle's treachery.  A must read for anyone who has in the least a twinkle of a sense of adventure.
      
